name: Fall Harvest Risotto with Garlic Shrimp

steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Chop the garlic
- Cut leek in half lengthwise, wash, slice leek, white part only (about 1 cup)
- Remove chard leaves from stems; chop leaved coarsely (2 cups) and chop 
- Crumble the cheese


### Steps
1. Preheat a large stockpot on medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minutes
2. Place oil in pot
3. Add the garlic, leeks, chard stems, and squash; cook for 2 to 3 minutes
4. Reduce the heat to medium
5. Stir in rice, bisque,  and broth until blended
6. Cover pot and cook for 10 minutes
7. Reduce heat to low and cook and stir for 20 minutes
8. Remove pan from heat 
9. Add in cheese and stir vigorously 
10. Prepare shrimp, while risotto cooks, follow the instructions on the box
11. Stir into the risotto the chard leaves, salt and pepper.
12. Plate the risotto and add some shrimp on top
